thread.title: Iron ore price jumps past $US55
thread.title_full: Iron ore price jumps past $US55 | Business Spectator

author: Daniel Palmer
title: Iron ore price jumps past $US55
text:
The price of iron ore has risen for a third straight day as commodities rebound on expectations of a delay to lift-off on US interest rates.
At the end of the latest session, benchmark iron ore for immediate delivery to the port of Tianjin in China was trading at $US55.50 a tonne, up 1.3 per cent from $US54.80 a tonne in the prior session.
The commodity has benefitted from the prospect of the US Federal Reserve holding off on an interest rate hike until 2016.
The potential delay has driven down the US dollar and spurred interest in risky asset classes such as stocks and commodities. However, the rally could be tested when Chinese trade and inflation data are released on Tuesday.
